summary:
Known issue with Visual Studio
        If you have used the Nuget package manager to manage this SDK visual studio fails to automatically copy the 'websocketsharp.dll' into your build directories during build
        Solution
        The solution to this issue is to directly reference the 'websocket-sharp.dll' in the project that is consuming the SDK.
        The 'websocket-sharp.dll' can be found in the packages folder packages\DoshiiPosDotNetSDK.~currentVersion~\lib
        The above file must be referenced and set to copy local in your project.

description: SQLitePCL.raw is a Portable Class Library (PCL) for low-level (raw) access to SQLite.  This package does not provide an API which is friendly to app developers. (Note that with the 0.8.0 release, the package ID is changing from 'SQLitePCL.raw_basic' to 'SQLitePCL.raw'.  Eventually, the old ID will stop getting updates.)
